I'm sorry for the intrusion,

19:09.782 --> 19:12.450
but I need to talk to you about
your husband, travis bloom.

19:12.485 --> 19:14.485
- What is this about?

19:14.520 --> 19:17.788
- Mrs. Bloom, when was the
last time you saw your husband?

19:23.395 --> 19:24.995
- My husband likes to drink.

19:25.030 --> 19:27.264
Sometimes he disappears
for days--goes on a bender.

19:27.299 --> 19:28.666
- So three days ago?

19:28.701 --> 19:30.767
That was the last time
you saw him?

19:30.803 --> 19:32.369
- I've been calling him,
leaving messages.

19:32.404 --> 19:34.605
He hasn't gotten back to me.

19:34.640 --> 19:36.207
- Is that normal?

19:36.242 --> 19:38.442
Your husband doesn't
return your calls?

19:38.477 --> 19:42.413
- We don't have
the best marriage.

19:42.448 --> 19:43.947
- Can you think of any reason

19:43.983 --> 19:46.850
why he may have wanted
to leave town?

19:46.885 --> 19:48.385
- Nope.

19:48.421 --> 19:50.721
- Can you think of anyone who
may want to harm your husband?

19:50.756 --> 19:52.556
- No.

19:52.591 --> 19:54.257
- Mrs. Bloom,
the reason I'm here

19:54.293 --> 19:57.328
is because your husband
is known to police.

19:57.363 --> 19:59.196
- What does that mean?

19:59.232 --> 20:01.265
- Well, we believe
he's dealing drugs,

20:01.300 --> 20:03.133
right out of this warehouse,
in fact.

20:03.168 --> 20:04.802
- You can't be serious.

20:04.837 --> 20:06.737
- You haven't seen
anything suspicious?

20:06.772 --> 20:08.105
- I'm very involved
in the business.

20:08.140 --> 20:10.241
I would know if something
like that was happening.

20:12.945 --> 20:16.113
- Well, I'd say
it's a big place.

20:16.148 --> 20:18.015
You sure?

20:18.050 --> 20:20.184
- Well, a person can
never know everything,

20:20.219 --> 20:22.586
but yes, I'm pretty sure.

20:22.621 --> 20:24.455
- Okay.

20:26.825 --> 20:28.725
Look, ma'am,
I'm sorry to be the one

20:28.761 --> 20:30.060
to have to lay this
all on you.

20:30.095 --> 20:31.728
- Well, you're just
doing your job.

20:31.763 --> 20:33.631
- Maybe I could drive you
down to the station,

20:33.666 --> 20:36.967
help you fill out
a missing persons report.

20:37.003 --> 20:39.003
- He's only been
gone a few days.

20:39.038 --> 20:41.572
He's disappeared for longer.
I'm sure he'll be back.

20:41.607 --> 20:46.877
- Okay, well, if there's
anything, just call.

20:48.747 --> 20:50.647
- I will.

20:50.683 --> 20:54.251
- You don't seem
to worried, ma'am.

20:54.287 --> 20:56.253
About your husband?

20:56.288 --> 20:58.956
- I process my emotions
in a very private way.

21:00.826 --> 21:02.994
- Okay.

21:21.447 --> 21:25.282
- How are you, brendan?

21:25.318 --> 21:29.153
- I'm gonna die here,
pretty doctor mary harris.

21:29.188 --> 21:31.255
- Chemo's working.

21:31.290 --> 21:33.624
- It's making me sicker.

21:33.659 --> 21:37.494
- It's buying you time.

21:37.529 --> 21:41.331
- I've never given up
on anything in my life,

21:41.367 --> 21:43.000
but I feel like giving up.

21:47.840 --> 21:50.007
- Maybe giving up is okay.

21:50.043 --> 21:53.344
- Then why does
it feel so bad?

21:53.379 --> 21:57.714
Like I'm not being
true to myself?

21:57.750 --> 22:00.850
- You can stop the chemo,
go home,

22:00.886 --> 22:03.987
be with germaine,
with family.

22:04.023 --> 22:06.190
- Just lie there
and wait to die?

22:11.664 --> 22:13.631
I didn't think
I'd go out like this.

22:19.271 --> 22:21.404
- In mexico, they have
a festival called

22:21.440 --> 22:23.874
the day of the dead.

22:23.909 --> 22:26.276
There are parades,

22:26.312 --> 22:28.311
and people bring food
to the cemeteries

22:28.347 --> 22:32.015
to encourage the souls
of the dead to visit.

22:32.051 --> 22:33.617
It's a celebration.

22:33.652 --> 22:35.986
- A fiesta.
- Yes.

22:36.021 --> 22:38.856
- Hmm.
- Death isn't bad.

22:38.891 --> 22:41.825
It doesn't have to be.

22:41.860 --> 22:44.828
It's part of life.

22:44.864 --> 22:48.265
And you can say good-bye
the way you want,

22:48.300 --> 22:51.535
live your death
as you would your life.

22:51.570 --> 22:54.104
- I would want it
to be a party.

22:54.139 --> 22:56.040
- It can be.

22:56.075 --> 22:57.541
- Like a performance.

23:07.653 --> 23:09.653
- All right, come on.

23:09.689 --> 23:12.856
You got this.
- Yeah.

23:12.891 --> 23:14.624
- Excuse me.

23:14.660 --> 23:17.394
If I were to flirt with you,
what would be my best approach?

23:17.430 --> 23:18.829
Nothing too creepy.

23:18.864 --> 23:21.732
Just as a teachable moment
for my young friend here.

23:21.767 --> 23:26.069
- Okay. You could ask me
if my eyes are hazel or brown.

23:26.105 --> 23:28.238
- Are your eyes
hazel or brown?

23:28.274 --> 23:30.441
- They're brown.

23:30.476 --> 23:32.076
- Thank you.

23:34.947 --> 23:37.147
See? It's easy.

23:37.183 --> 23:39.649
- Yeah, maybe for you
with your james bond accent.

23:39.685 --> 23:42.919
- It's not my accent.
It's my charm.

23:42.954 --> 23:44.487
Oh, is that
your lady friend?

23:44.523 --> 23:46.223
- Oh, my god, oh, my god.
What do I do?

23:46.258 --> 23:47.725
What do I do? What do I do?
- Calm down.

23:47.760 --> 23:48.892
You can't have
sex until you've had

23:48.928 --> 23:50.794
a conversation,
so talk to her.

23:50.829 --> 23:52.429
- This was such a stupid idea.

23:52.464 --> 23:54.531
- You got this. Come on.

23:54.567 --> 23:57.902
- Hi, joshua.
- Hey, kailey.

23:57.937 --> 24:00.270
- Is this your nurse?

24:00.305 --> 24:03.340
- More of
a spiritual advisor.

24:03.376 --> 24:04.941
You've got this.

24:04.977 --> 24:06.844
I'll be over there
loitering nonchalantly.

24:06.879 --> 24:09.646
Wave if you need me
to ollie on over.

24:09.681 --> 24:12.315
- That's not what ollie means.

24:12.351 --> 24:14.485
- Good to know.

24:18.858 --> 24:21.825
<i> [gentle music]</i>

24:21.860 --> 24:28.833
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:30.536 --> 24:33.870
- so are your eyes
hazel or brown?

24:33.906 --> 24:36.206
- They're blue.

24:36.242 --> 24:38.008
[both chuckle]

24:38.043 --> 24:40.010
- right.

24:45.050 --> 24:47.017
- Out.

24:51.724 --> 24:53.823
- Whoa. Wait.
What are you doing?

24:53.859 --> 24:56.293
- Well, this is what my mom
used to do with me and mary.

24:56.328 --> 24:58.395
Solve whatever's going
on between you.

24:58.431 --> 25:01.665
- You're literally
marooning us on an island!

25:12.177 --> 25:14.345
Your aunt's actually pretty
gangster leaving us out here.

25:33.165 --> 25:35.565
Why are you so mad at me?
Huh?

25:35.600 --> 25:36.867
- I don't want
to talk to you.

25:36.902 --> 25:39.836
- Oh, what, jess?
Is it because I kissed you?

25:39.871 --> 25:42.706
- What do you think?

25:42.741 --> 25:45.009
- That wasn't--

25:45.044 --> 25:47.011
that was just for fun.

25:51.716 --> 25:54.518
- Do you want to be with me?

25:54.553 --> 25:56.086
- I don't know.

25:56.121 --> 25:57.655
- Do you want to be
in a relationship with me?

25:57.690 --> 25:59.623
- We are in
a relationship, jess.

25:59.658 --> 26:03.360
- No, do you want to be
my girlfriend?

26:03.395 --> 26:07.197
No, of course you don't.
You're not even gay.

26:07.232 --> 26:13.603
I am, and you just can't
let anyone be happy.

26:13.638 --> 26:15.471
- That's not true.

26:15.507 --> 26:17.307
I could ruin
your life right now,

26:17.343 --> 26:20.811
and by not doing that,
I am making you happy.

26:23.082 --> 26:25.749
- I'm done. I'm done.
I am so done.

26:25.784 --> 26:28.685
I'm done playing
all your stupid games.

26:28.721 --> 26:31.822
- What are you doing?
Jess!

26:31.857 --> 26:33.323
Jess!

26:33.358 --> 26:36.260
What, you can't just
leave me here alone!

26:36.295 --> 26:39.095
<i> [gentle music]</i>

26:39.130 --> 26:44.100
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:44.136 --> 26:47.837
- what's it like being sick?

26:47.873 --> 26:50.474
Like, knowing that you're...

26:50.509 --> 26:52.776
- That I'm dying?

26:52.811 --> 26:55.145
- Yeah.

26:58.283 --> 27:00.851
- Do you remember this
birthday party I had?

27:00.886 --> 27:02.586
I think we were, like, ten,

27:02.621 --> 27:06.756
and my parents got me this
piñata shaped like a turtle.

27:06.792 --> 27:08.792
- Vaguely.
- Right.

27:08.827 --> 27:11.661
Well, they blindfolded us,
spun us around,

27:11.697 --> 27:15.032
and kind of let us loose.

27:15.067 --> 27:17.100
You couldn't see shit,

27:17.135 --> 27:19.870
and you were swinging
around a bat like crazy

27:19.905 --> 27:24.707
just trying to get
all this candy.

27:24.743 --> 27:27.745
I don't know.
It's kind of like that.

28:04.582 --> 28:07.251
- Young love.
Hey. I did that.

28:10.756 --> 28:14.091
- Oh.
Sorry, kailey. I got...

28:14.126 --> 28:17.127
- Josh? Nurse?
Or whoever you are.

28:17.162 --> 28:18.996
Can you help him?
- Josh? Josh?

28:19.031 --> 28:21.999
Hang on.

28:22.034 --> 28:24.401
Joshua, mate, you okay?

28:24.437 --> 28:26.703
Now we need to get you
to a hospital.

28:26.739 --> 28:32.208
- No, des. I'm good.
You were right about today.

28:32.244 --> 28:35.912
I'm ready for what
you promised me.

28:35.947 --> 28:37.881
- I got rid
of the medicine, josh.

28:37.916 --> 28:39.883
- What?

28:44.756 --> 28:46.690
- [groans]

28:46.725 --> 28:49.693
okay. Okay. Please.

28:49.728 --> 28:51.862
Pick up, mary. Pick up.

28:51.897 --> 28:53.897
<i> [line ringing]</i>

28:53.932 --> 28:55.232
<i> - hello?</i>

28:55.267 --> 28:58.502
- I need you to bring me
some medicine--the medicine.

28:58.537 --> 29:01.871
- Why?
<i> - I chucked all mine.</i>

29:01.907 --> 29:05.242
I'm with a kid
named joshua yang.

29:07.513 --> 29:11.381
- A kid?
<i> - He's terminally ill.</i>

29:11.416 --> 29:14.218
He's a pain in the ass,

29:14.253 --> 29:17.587
but he's mostly--

29:17.623 --> 29:19.590
he's why we do this.

29:21.693 --> 29:23.093
- Where should I meet you?

29:23.129 --> 29:26.162
<i> - Go to his house.</i>
<i> I'll text you his address.</i>

29:26.197 --> 29:28.165
- Okay.

29:33.805 --> 29:36.807
- Okay, boss.
We're in.

29:36.842 --> 29:39.109
Olivia's warehouse is
completely wired for sound.

29:39.144 --> 29:41.010
- Good.

29:41.046 --> 29:44.314
- You know, it was like she
thought she was above it all.

29:44.350 --> 29:46.549
She barely tried
to fake any feeling.

29:46.585 --> 29:48.184
- Oh, she's definitely
a player.

29:48.220 --> 29:50.520
You were right about her,

29:50.555 --> 29:52.555
and you were right
about mary harris.

29:52.591 --> 29:54.457
- You put a team on mary?
- Yeah.

29:54.493 --> 29:56.326
She just left
the hospital, early.

29:56.362 --> 29:59.129
Something's definitely up.

29:59.164 --> 30:03.100
- Good. Let's hope
she leads us to travis.

30:03.135 --> 30:06.102
<i> [tense music]</i>

30:06.137 --> 30:13.110
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:20.519 --> 30:23.320
[dialing]

30:23.355 --> 30:24.520
<i> - yeah, mary.</i>

30:24.556 --> 30:26.322
- Des, we need a new plan.

30:26.358 --> 30:27.858
<i> - What? Why?</i>

30:27.893 --> 30:29.960
- I'm being followed.

30:34.366 --> 30:37.333
<i> [gentle music]</i>

30:37.368 --> 30:43.907
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:43.942 --> 30:45.475
- you know your mom
would kill me

30:45.510 --> 30:47.276
if you drowned, right?

30:47.312 --> 30:49.246
- She doesn't even
have time to punish me.

30:49.281 --> 30:50.780
She probably
wouldn't notice.

30:50.816 --> 30:53.049
- What? Your mom loves you,
you heinous little brat.

30:53.084 --> 30:54.985
What are--
what is wrong with you?

30:55.020 --> 30:57.520
- I was on the swim team.
I knew I could make it.

30:57.555 --> 30:59.456
- No.
What is wrong with you?

30:59.491 --> 31:01.692
Why are you acting
like somebody else?

31:03.696 --> 31:05.762
- I don't know.

31:05.797 --> 31:07.397
- Is it your
bad influence bestie?

31:07.433 --> 31:10.834
- No. She's the least
of my problems.

31:10.869 --> 31:13.070
- Then what?

31:15.807 --> 31:18.408
- My mom.

31:18.443 --> 31:21.345
I feel like I never know
what's going on with her.

31:21.380 --> 31:24.648
I can't talk to her about
what's going on with me.

31:24.683 --> 31:28.985
I feel like she's
always lying to me.

31:29.021 --> 31:31.521
Like this morning,
she went out early,

31:31.556 --> 31:34.124
and she said it was
for work, but I--

31:34.159 --> 31:37.860
I know it wasn't, and...

31:37.896 --> 31:40.564
I don't know, it just makes me
feel like I'm a crazy person.

31:45.504 --> 31:48.238
- Do you know why my mom
would put us on that island?

31:48.274 --> 31:49.505
- To punish you.

31:49.541 --> 31:53.844
- No, I made that shit up.

31:53.879 --> 31:56.279
She would get really
depressed sometimes,

31:56.314 --> 32:00.550
and she couldn't look
after me and mary.

32:00.586 --> 32:01.952
- Really?
- Yeah.

32:01.987 --> 32:03.987
So she would put us
on the island

32:04.022 --> 32:06.223
to kind of protect us
from her,

32:06.258 --> 32:07.990
which is kind of
what I think your mom does

32:08.026 --> 32:09.960
with you sometimes.

32:09.995 --> 32:12.662
- She neglects us
because she cares?

32:12.697 --> 32:14.364
- She protects you
from parts of herself

32:14.399 --> 32:16.333
that she feels are dangerous.

32:16.368 --> 32:19.903
- Like what?

32:19.938 --> 32:23.073
- You just need to work
that out with her.

32:23.108 --> 32:26.075
<i> [gentle music]</i>

32:26.110 --> 32:29.145
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:29.180 --> 32:30.813
- keep walking.
You can do it.

32:30.849 --> 32:31.914
We're almost there.

32:31.950 --> 32:35.051
- His house is
just through here.

32:35.087 --> 32:37.587
- That kiss you gave
kailey was epic.

32:37.622 --> 32:39.456
You charmed her, my friend.

32:39.491 --> 32:41.658
- Couple more weeks and I
would have gone all the way.

32:41.694 --> 32:43.427
- The student
becomes the teacher.

32:43.462 --> 32:45.328
I'm proud of you, man.

32:45.363 --> 32:49.132
- Okay, casanova.
Just a few more steps.

32:54.773 --> 32:57.640
- Hello?
Anybody home?

32:57.675 --> 33:00.444
- Joshua!

33:00.479 --> 33:02.678
Who are these people?

33:02.714 --> 33:06.649
- These are the doctors
I was telling you about, mom.

33:06.685 --> 33:09.486
- I'm technically not a doctor.
She is, though.

33:09.521 --> 33:12.989
Doctor mary. I'm desmond.

33:13.024 --> 33:14.624
- We're death counselors.

33:14.660 --> 33:17.794
We're here to honor your son's
wish to die with dignity.

33:21.600 --> 33:24.200
- We discussed it.

33:24.235 --> 33:26.036
We support our son's wish.

33:28.240 --> 33:32.308
- Does it have to be today?
Just one more day.

33:32.344 --> 33:34.511
That's all we want.

33:36.948 --> 33:41.218
- Joshua, one more day?

33:41.253 --> 33:44.588
It's possible.
Do you want to wait?

33:44.623 --> 33:46.389
- No.

33:46.425 --> 33:49.025
I'm ready to go.

33:49.060 --> 33:50.393
- We would come back.

33:50.428 --> 33:52.495
You know we wouldn't
let you down.

33:52.530 --> 33:55.498
- No, I know, but...

33:55.534 --> 33:58.434
Today was a good day.

33:58.470 --> 34:01.238
My only good day
since my diagnosis.

34:08.713 --> 34:11.915
- I hear you've been
collecting quotes on death.

34:11.950 --> 34:15.351
Want to know my favorite?

34:15.386 --> 34:19.723
"dying is a wild night
and a new road."

34:24.930 --> 34:27.564
- I'm not afraid.

34:31.937 --> 34:34.770
- You should talk to
your parents now.

34:34.806 --> 34:38.040
Des and I will be ready
when you are.

34:38.076 --> 34:40.710
We'll give you some privacy.

34:45.717 --> 34:50.420
- Mom, dad,
will you let me go?

34:50.455 --> 34:53.423
<i> [somber music]</i>

34:53.458 --> 35:00.430
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:03.868 --> 35:05.836
[indistinct radio chatter]

35:08.239 --> 35:09.739
- let's do this.

35:09.774 --> 35:12.742
<i> [intense music]</i>

35:12.777 --> 35:19.682
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:19.717 --> 35:21.584
police.

35:21.619 --> 35:23.853
- What?
- What's going on?

35:23.888 --> 35:25.421
- The police are here.

35:25.456 --> 35:27.491
Hey.
Where are you going?

35:34.132 --> 35:36.500
- Do you know where mary is?

35:44.642 --> 35:47.344
- Des, I've been thinking.

35:47.379 --> 35:50.179
If the cops come,
if they find us,

35:50.214 --> 35:52.148
I'll say it was all me.

35:52.183 --> 35:54.450
- We're in this together.

35:54.486 --> 35:57.654
I believe you're what
they call my ride or die.

36:00.792 --> 36:02.992
But mary, I love this part.

36:03.027 --> 36:04.928
I love it.

36:04.963 --> 36:06.596
It gives me purpose.

36:06.631 --> 36:08.798
It makes me feel like
I'm doing good in the world.

36:08.834 --> 36:11.200
- Me too.

36:11.235 --> 36:14.303
- But the other part--
the part that you like--

36:14.339 --> 36:16.672
- this is the part I like.
- Is it?

36:16.708 --> 36:18.674
Not the skulking around
away from the law?

36:18.710 --> 36:20.911
The threatening drug lords?

36:23.548 --> 36:26.349
- What we do isn't legal.
Things creep in.

36:26.385 --> 36:31.320
- Yeah, I'm aware, but mary,
let's do the death retreat.

36:31.356 --> 36:33.723
- Your idea where we pretend
to open a hospice

36:33.759 --> 36:34.924
and kill people en masse?

36:34.960 --> 36:36.726
- Yes.

36:36.762 --> 36:38.995
Because I can do this,

36:39.030 --> 36:41.731
but the rest of it,
the criminal shit,

36:41.766 --> 36:44.166
the bad shit,

36:44.202 --> 36:45.902
that's my line.

36:49.641 --> 36:51.274
- Okay.
- Ready?

36:51.309 --> 36:52.375
- Yep.

36:54.112 --> 36:57.681
But I won't let you
go to jail again.

36:57.716 --> 36:59.683
That's my line.

37:28.212 --> 37:32.047
- Hey. Josh.

37:32.083 --> 37:34.217
This is for old time's sake.

37:37.556 --> 37:39.522
- Thank you.

38:03.982 --> 38:06.949
<i> [somber music]</i>

38:06.984 --> 38:13.957
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:30.075 --> 38:33.109
- I love you, joshua.

38:33.144 --> 38:35.945
- I love you too.

38:35.980 --> 38:42.852
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:58.669 --> 39:02.071
- he'll slip away now.
It's peaceful.

39:02.106 --> 39:09.079
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:02.701 --> 40:04.901
- go.

40:11.676 --> 40:14.644
<i> [kyson's "you" plays]</i>

40:14.679 --> 40:21.083
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:21.119 --> 40:23.085
<i> - ♪ no man's an island ♪</i>

